  </section>
  <section line_height="10.91" font="KCQPMK+CMR10" letter_ratio="0.12"
year_ratio="0.0" cap_ratio="0.18" name_ratio="0.2702702702702703"
word_count="74" lateness="0.95" reference_score="23.89">
    <line x_offset="0.0" y_offset="67.8" spacing="0.0">Figure 7: The
normalized inverse of the generalized ergodic measure</line>
    <line x_offset="0.0" y_offset="54.24" spacing="2.65">d (0)/d (n) as a
function of the number of Monte Carlo steps n calcu-</line>
    <line x_offset="5.64" y_offset="53.3" spacing="-7.02">VV</line>
    <line x_offset="0.0" y_offset="40.68" spacing="1.71">lated for &#x3B3;
= 0.9 potential at &#x3B2; = 10 using the standard Monte Carlo
scheme</line>
    <line x_offset="0.0" y_offset="27.12" spacing="2.65">(q = 1) and the
generalized Monte Carlo scheme (q = 1.5, 2.5). d (0)/d (n)</line>
    <line x_offset="303.96" y_offset="26.18" spacing="-7.02">VV</line>
    <line x_offset="0.0" y_offset="13.56" spacing="1.71">grows linearly
with the Monte Carlo steps n and the diffusion is faster for</line>
    <line x_offset="0.0" y_offset="0.0" spacing="2.65">larger q.</line>
    <component x="125.76" y="212.19" width="358.72" height="78.71"
