  </section>
  <section line_height="10.91" font="KCQPMK+CMR10" letter_ratio="0.06"
year_ratio="0.0" cap_ratio="0.16" name_ratio="0.2753623188405797"
word_count="69" lateness="1.0" reference_score="22.91">
    <line x_offset="0.0" y_offset="67.68" spacing="0.0">Figure 8: The
diffusion constant D as a function of temperature &#x3B2;. (a) A</line>
    <line x_offset="167.28" y_offset="66.73" spacing="-7.02">V</line>
    <line x_offset="0.0" y_offset="54.12" spacing="1.71">straight line of
the semi-log plot of D vs &#x3B2; for the standard Monte Carlo</line>
    <line x_offset="180.6" y_offset="53.17" spacing="-7.02">V</line>
    <line x_offset="0.0" y_offset="40.56" spacing="1.71">scheme indicates
activation-type diffusion, while (b) straight lines of the log-</line>
    <line x_offset="0.0" y_offset="27.0" spacing="2.65">log plot for the
Tsallis Monte Carlo scheme in the high temperature region</line>
    <line x_offset="0.0" y_offset="13.44" spacing="2.65">indicate slow
power-law decrease of the diffusion constant as the temperature</line>
    <line x_offset="0.0" y_offset="0.0" spacing="2.53">is lowered (larger
&#x3B2;).</line>
    <component x="125.76" y="272.07" width="358.77" height="78.59"
page="20" page_width="612.0" page_height="792.0"/>
  </section>
